.TH "ARCHIVE_COLOR" "1" "2025-10-29" "" "ARCHIVE_COLOR Manual"
.SH "NAME"
\*[self] \- color tar output like ls does
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
tar tvzf
.I "tarball.tar.gz"
.RB "| " "\*[self]"
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
\*[self] is a modified tarcolor that also works for
other archive listings such as rpm, debian, ar, and isoinfo archives.
.PP
Colors output of
.B "tar tvf"
similarly to the way GNU
.B "ls"
(in GNU coreutils) would color a directory listing.
.PP
Colors can be customized using an environment variable:
.PP
.RS 4
.EX
TAR_COLORS='di=01;34:ln=01;36:ex=01;32:so=01;40:pi=01;40:bd=40;33:cd=40;33:su=0;41:sg=0;46'
.EE
.RE
.PP
The format for TAR_COLORS is similar to the format used by LS_COLORS. Check out the
.URL "http://geoff.greer.fm/lscolors/" "online LSCOLORS generator" "."
.SH "OPTIONS"
.TP
.B "\-h  \-\-help"
Print help text and exit. Optional.
